@baseUrl = http://localhost:3100/api
@usernameSuccess = userA
@usernameFail = userB
@usernameCooldown = userC

### Check current flash sale status.
### Use this first to confirm seeded sale exists and to see available slots/start-end time.
GET {{baseUrl}}/flash-sale/status

###

### Happy path: user attempts to buy and should receive a reservationId.
### This request is named so later variables can read from its latest response.
# @name buySuccess
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders/buy
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{usernameSuccess}}"
}

###

@reservationIdSuccess = {{buySuccess.response.body.$.reservationId}}

###


### Check status after reservation.
### Should return `reserved` while reservation is still active.
GET {{baseUrl}}/orders/status?username={{usernameSuccess}}

###

### Happy path payment success.
### Uses reservationId captured from `buySuccess`.
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders/pay
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{usernameSuccess}}",
  "reservationId": "{{reservationIdSuccess}}",
  "forceSuccess": true
}

###

### Check status after successful payment.
### Should return `paid`.
GET {{baseUrl}}/orders/status?username={{usernameSuccess}}

###

### Attempt to buy again after already paying.
### Should return `already_paid`.
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders/buy
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{usernameSuccess}}"
}

###

### Failure path: second user attempts to buy and gets a reservation.
### Named request + PR-style `@set`.
# @name buyFailUser
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders/buy
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{usernameFail}}"
}

###

@reservationIdFail = {{buyFailUser.response.body.$.reservationId}}

### Simulate payment failure.
### Reservation should stay active after this.
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders/pay
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{usernameFail}}",
  "reservationId": "{{reservationIdFail}}",
  "forceSuccess": false
}

###

### Check status after failed payment.
### Should still return `reserved` until reservation expires or payment later succeeds.
GET {{baseUrl}}/orders/status?username={{usernameFail}}

###

### Retry payment for same reservation, now force success.
### This shows payment retry while reservation is still active.
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders/pay
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{usernameFail}}",
  "reservationId": "{{reservationIdFail}}",
  "forceSuccess": true
}

###

### Invalid reservation scenario.
### Same user, wrong reservationId. Should return `invalid_reservation` or no reservation depending on state.
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders/pay
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{usernameFail}}",
  "reservationId": "wrong-reservation-id",
  "forceSuccess": true
}

###

### Cooldown / expiry scenario setup: reserve for a third user.
### Named request + PR-style `@set`.
# @name buyCooldownUser
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders/buy
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{usernameCooldown}}"
}

###

@reservationIdCooldown = buyCooldownUser.response.body.$.reservationId

### Check status for cooldown scenario user.
### Should return `reserved` immediately after buy.
GET {{baseUrl}}/orders/status?username={{usernameCooldown}}

###

### Manual wait step for expiry scenario.
### Wait 5 minutes for release-reservation job

### After reservation expiry, status should become `none`.
GET {{baseUrl}}/orders/status?username={{usernameCooldown}}

###

### After reservation expiry, buying again immediately should hit cooldown.
### Should return `cooldown_active` until cooldown TTL passes.
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders/buy
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{usernameCooldown}}"
}

###

### Manual wait step for cooldown expiry.
### Wait 2 minutes, then try buying again with same user.

### After cooldown expires, user should be able to reserve again.
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders/buy
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{usernameCooldown}}"
}

###

### User-throttle scenario.
### Run this request repeatedly 4 times within one minute for same username to trigger `too_many_requests`.
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders/buy
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "rate-limit-user"
}
